{"comments":"Tour state update function\n\nImplements the Elm-style update function for tour state transitions.\nAll state changes flow through this function, making the tour behavior\npredictable and testable.\n\n```\nState × Msg → State × [Cmd]\n```\n\n## State Transitions\n\n```\nTourInactive\n    │ StartTour\n    ▼\nTourActive(0)\n    │ NextStep\n    ▼\nTourActive(n)\n    │ NextStep (at last)\n    ▼\nTourCompleted\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```purescript\nimport Hydrogen.Tour.Update as Tour\n\n-- In your update function\nhandleAction :: Action -> H.HalogenM State Action () o m Unit\nhandleAction = case _ of\n  TourAction tourMsg -> do\n    result <- Tour.update tourMsg <$> H.gets _.tour\n    H.modify_ _ { tour = result.state }\n    traverse_ handleTourCmd result.cmds\n```\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"Pure update function for tour state\n\nGiven a message and current state, produces a new state and any commands\nthat should be executed. This is the heart of the Elm architecture pattern.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":{"identifier":"msg","kind":null,"skolem":null,"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Tour","State"],"TourMsg"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"msg","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Tour","State"],"TourState"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"msg","tag":"TypeVar"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Tour","Update"],"UpdateResult"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":"msg","tag":"TypeVar"}],"